Automated kidney stone segmentation from CT images using nnU-Net v2's self-configuring deep learning framework on the KSSD2025 dataset. Features 5-fold cross-validation, comprehensive evaluation metrics (Dice, F1, IoU/Jaccard, Precision, Recall, Sensitivity, Specificity, HD95, AUC-ROC), statistical significance testing (Wilcoxon signed-rank), convergence analysis, prediction visualization, method comparison table, and publication-ready figures. Surpasses the KSSD2025 Modified U-Net baseline with statistically significant improvement.
